      "writtenOn": "2020-07-28T17:22:58Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "I usually use something like p/x and cast the pointer to an array type.  I think there\u0027s some sort of @-related syntax too, not sure.\n\nI agree with Brian. I would prefer you to focus your effort on whatever debugging sidecars you need to work with SkTArray unchanged, or to convert code you want to debug to std::vector if that\u0027s straightforward.",
      "parentUuid": "e8444a73_b84926bb",
      "revId": "f2c235f6275ac1338adfd981f72b903093fbc4bd",
